---
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 px-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
  <div class="reveal">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-12">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-accent/70 uppercase tracking-widest">About</span>
      <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-border"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
    <!-- Text -->
    <div class="md:col-span-3 space-y-5 reveal">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold leading-tight">
        I write tools<br />
        <span class="text-accent">for people who design chips.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        My day job at Qualcomm is EDA software. I write Python tools that hardware engineers use
        to validate connectivity in chip designs. These tools sit in the critical path for tape-out,
        the point of no return in chip design. The chips my code helps validate are inside most
        Android phones made in the past few years, and the ones shipping in the years to come.
        That's something few software engineers can say.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        On the side I've been building in the LLM space: a Text-to-SQL pipeline exploring different
        RAG strategies and LangGraph orchestration patterns, and an
        <a href="https://selimym.github.io/data_privacy_distopia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
           class="text-accent hover:text-text transition-colors underline underline-offset-2">educational browser game</a>
        about how surveillance systems get normalized. I also co-authored a 2025 ML paper on molecular generation.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        My users are hardware engineers on tape-out deadlines. They have zero tolerance for bugs.
        That shapes how I think about software quality.
      </p>

      <!-- Publication -->
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg bg-surface border border-border text-sm text-muted">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
        </svg>
        Co-author, <span class="text-text font-medium">MGOL: Molecule Generation with Ordering Loss</span> &mdash; 2025
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Stats -->
    <div class="md:col-span-2 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 reveal">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-1">4<span class="text-accent">+</span></div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Years production Python at Qualcomm</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-1">$2<span class="text-accent">M+</span></div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Annual licensing costs saved</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-1">140<span class="text-accent">+</span></div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Chip designers using my tools daily</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stat-card {
    @apply p-5 rounded-xl bg-surface border border-border hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors;
  }
</style>
